Uses of Package
com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener

  • Packages that use com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener 
    Package Description
    com.noctarius.tengi.client
    The client package contains classes necessary to create a client instance inside applications.
    com.noctarius.tengi.core.connection
    The connection package contains the common interfaces to work with server or client connections.
    com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener
    The listener package contains the common listener interfaces for messages (MessageListener) and any kind of connection events (ConnectionListener as well as broken down interfaces for Java 8 support.
    com.noctarius.tengi.server
    The server package contains classes necessary to create a server instance inside applications.
    com.noctarius.tengi.spi.connection
    The connection package contains interfaces and base-classes necessary to implement custom transports using the provided SPI.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener used by com.noctarius.tengi.client 
    Class and Description
    ConnectedListener
    The ConnectedListener defines handlers that are able to handle connect events of connections to setup application state for this connection or allocate additional resource.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener used by com.noctarius.tengi.core.connection 
    Class and Description
    Listener 
    MessageListener
    The MessageListener interfaces describes a handler that is able to handle arriving messages and handle them accordingly.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener used by com.noctarius.tengi.core.listener 
    Class and Description
    ClosedListener
    The ClosedListener defines handlers that are able to handle close events of connections.
    DisconnectedListener
    The DisconnectedListener defines handlers that are able to handle disconnect events of connections to clean up application state, free resources or similar actions.
    ExceptionListener
    The ExceptionListener defines handlers that are able to handle exceptions thrown from any operation based on a known connection.
